<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/ TRACTION CONTROL TROUBLESHOOTING: BENDIX - 9100, 9200, 9300 and 9400 Models Built March 1,
        1998 and After - TROUBLESHOOTING - TESTING TRACTION CONTROL MODULATOR, PART A
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="test" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TESTING TRACTION CONTROL MODULATOR, PART A</title>
        <para>Perform
            <emph type="bold">
                <hotlnk document="s04042_7.xml" xrefid="t0404201">INITIAL START-UP TEST PROCEDURE
                    <xref refid="t0404201"/>
                </hotlnk>
            </emph>
            before performing this test.
        </para>
        <table id="t0404221" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Traction Control Modulator, Part A</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.52in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.68in"/>
                <colspec colname="COLSPEC2" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.88in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="1.59in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="6" spanname="s1t6" align="center"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>STEP</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>KEY</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>ACTION</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="COLSPEC2">
                            <para>TEST POINTS</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>YES / IN SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>NO / OUT OF SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Inspect controller for illuminated LEDs. Note if the TRC and MOD LEDs are ON.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="COLSPEC2">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>TRC and MOD LEDs ON.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to
                                <hotlnk document="s04042_29.xml" xrefid="t0404223">TESTING J1922 DATA LINK CIRCUITS TO
                                    ENGINE ECM
                                    <xref refid="t0404223"/>
                                </hotlnk>
                                .
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remove connector (350) from controller. Measure resistance between terminals D3 and
                                D2.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="COLSPEC2">
                            <para>(350), D2 to D3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>10 to 12 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to
                                <hotlnk document="s04042_28.xml" xrefid="t0404222">TESTING TRACTION CONTROL MODULATOR,
                                    PART B
                                    <xref refid="t0404222"/>
                                </hotlnk>
                                .
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect 2-way traction control solenoid connector (360) located at the
                                controller/relay valve. At the connector measure resistance across the two terminals.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="COLSPEC2">
                            <para>(360), 1 to 2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>10 to 12 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Replace the traction control solenoid (part of the controller/relay assembly).</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>With connectors (350) and (360) disconnected, at (350) measure resistance between
                                terminals D3 and D2, and between these circuits and all other circuits in connector
                                (350). There should be resistance greater than 100K Ohms between these circuits or
                                between any other circuits in the connector.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="COLSPEC2">
                            <para>(350), D2 to D3 and to 16 other term.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Locate short between any circuits where resistance between terminals is 100K ohms or
                                less, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (350) use test lead to jumper terminal D3 to ground. At connector (360)
                                measure resistance to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="COLSPEC2">
                            <para>(360), 2 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Locate open in terminal D3 between connectors (350) and (360), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (350) use test lead to jumper terminal D2 to ground. At connector (360)
                                measure resistance to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="COLSPEC2">
                            <para>(360), 1 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Locate open in terminal D2 between connectors (350) and (360), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
